column7:
“I’m referring to it as World War C – world war against the coronavirus.” - 
@DrTomFrieden

He discusses our global response to #COVID19 with @DrKellyHenning and what we need to do to win this war. https://t.co/xZxj4W5rTX https://t.co/EYynMQr7oq

More time at home means more time to learn.

@JohnsHopkins is hosting a free online course on the COVID-19 pandemic. It’s an opportunity to understand the virus that has put the world on hold. 

Take the course: https://t.co/rDRUDRHBdM https://t.co/I6efy4UnwR

For decades, @RESCUEorg has come to the aid of millions of people displaced by conflict and crisis.

Amid the pandemic, their work has taken on new urgency. 

@BloombergDotOrg is committing $10 million to the IRC as they help save lives around the world. https://t.co/e8Vww0MTYw https://t.co/gRyEOZElI8

To safely reopen New York, we need to find and isolate the virus.

@NYGovCuomo and @BloombergDotOrg are building a contact tracing program that will hire an army of tracers to get us back on our feet.

Working together, New Yorkers will get through this. https://t.co/kw6BwtDr2m

Wherever there are @NYCHealthSystem front line workers supporting each other—like at NYC Health + Hospitals/Woodhull in Brooklyn—there is also 
@WCKitchen and @BloombergDotOrg waiting to serve them. 

Thank you for being in the fight to save lives. https://t.co/pVhX62bcO4

Trump has no strategy for testing &amp; tracing #COVID19. 

As @ksheekey explains, we are the only country in the developed world without a national plan.

@BloombergDotOrg &amp; @JohnsHopkinsSPH are stepping up to provide a tracing plan all states can use. https://t.co/DbX52Iy0io

Global challenges require global cooperation. 

@BloombergDotOrg is collaborating with @EU_Commission &amp; @glblctzn for Global Goal: Unite for Our Future—to help find a vaccine &amp; ensure everyone, everywhere has access to testing &amp; treatment for #COVID19. 
https://t.co/AOYvrlfXiY https://t.co/c049fhp8Ee

In a public health crisis, data is vital.

@BloombergDotOrg is releasing the COVID-19 Management Metrics for Cities to provide data tools for #localgov to better manage pandemic response, help cities focus their resources - and save lives. 
https://t.co/CEvtaiSbld

Cities are adapting to the pandemic, and transportation is a vital part of that response.

@BloombergDotOrg &amp; @NACTO are awarding 10 cities grants to make city streets safer &amp; more equitable.

This is a chance to move forward. https://t.co/gjXc0EtrC6

100,000 oil &amp; gas workers have been laid off this year.

We can fight climate change &amp; create jobs by employing these Americans to clean up gas wells that are leaking methane.

@JoeBiden &amp; @SpeakerPelosi support the idea - &amp; Senate Republicans should, too. https://t.co/U2clDk6ug0

Amid a pandemic, Trump is on the side of polluters.

@JoeBiden is on the side of people. 

The choice could not be more clear. https://t.co/HnrUfGgw0v

Californians are on the frontlines of the climate crisis.
 
@GavinNewsom’s bold plan to eliminate gas-powered vehicles will reduce deadly air pollution &amp; help to prevent more extreme weather-fueled tragedies like the wildfires.

https://t.co/eTWp5ag2X1

Americans are tired of Donald Trump’s chaos. 

@JoeBiden and @KamalaHarris will bring steady leadership and unity to a country in need of both.

That’s why I’m glad to work with @PrioritiesUSA and @VoteBlackPAC to let voters know what’s at stake in this election. https://t.co/dpTiubRB5q

Managing a pandemic starts with reliable and accurate data. It’s why the @JohnsHopkins Coronavirus Resource Center is so important – and why it made the @TIME 100 Best Inventions of 2020. 

@BloombergDotOrg is glad to support this critical resource. 
https://t.co/kH64P9fW6k

In 2002, after September 11, the @Tribeca Festival helped bring New York back.

In 2021, it has the power to do it again. 

@BloombergDotOrg has been proud to support the festival from the start. https://t.co/DTimWTN6vy

What is @COP26?

Every year, 197 countries come together to agree on a path for climate action. This year, they'll meet in Glasgow to assess progress on the Paris Agreement.

@BloombergDotOrg's Ailun Yang answers your questions in our new video series, "Countdown to COP": https://t.co/ECgKUD66SB

Gun deaths hit an all-time high in 2020.

We shouldn't live in fear of gun violence in our schools, offices, homes, and streets.

@Everytown's work to end gun violence is as important as ever. Join us by texting ACT to 644-33. https://t.co/Nw88fGKhfh
